Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories In the lead up to World Toilet Day, Domestos are raising awareness of the impact of poor sanitation in South Africa. By using the hashtag #WeArePissedOff, South Africans are encouraged to support the initiative and make a change.Glen Lewis, Metro FM DJ; Khaya Dlanga, author and blogger and Trevor Gumbi, stand-up comedian and actor, have all lent their voices to the crisis and have taken a stand with Domestos against the state of sanitation in South African public schools - restoring the dignity of the pupils.Visit here&nbsp;for more on the #WeArePissedOff campaign and its events.